    "assignee": null,
    "body": "This is not really an issue but I noticed that a lot of examples use a simple function to find blocks around the player and I think it's a common requirement for bots, however Mineflayer has no built-in method for that.\r\n\r\n[Darthfett/mineflayer-blockFinder](https://github.com/Darthfett/mineflayer-blockFinder) basically does the same thing and it's probably more flexible and efficient, but wouldn't it be better if there was a fallback method?\r\n\r\nIt would be really simple to implement and it would be used the same way, so it can be easily overridden by the blockFinder plugin without changing any code if the user wants a more efficient version of the same method, this would be specified in the documentation.\r\n\r\nThis would also simplify some of the examples by removing some duplicate code.\r\n\r\nI've already made a method that behaves like that for one of my bots, so if it is a good idea I could submit a pull request.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2015-07-21T04:27:54Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "Mineflayer should be the lowest API necessary to implement higher-level stuff. A block finder is fairly high-level and can be implemented without too much trouble with the methods mineflayer exposes. As such, it shouldn't be added in. If a user needs a blockFinder, he should use a mineflayer plugin to do it (or re-invent the wheel, which is what the examples do ^^).",
